      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk if anyone else notices this but the pigeons in the park have been doing this weird circling pattern every morning at like 7am. it's not just random flying, they're almost like they're signaling something about the pressure changes before the rain hits. i swear i can actually feel the shift when they do it. am i crazy or is there something going on with how they communicate?",
